WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.370 --> 00:00:08.150
MATTHIEU RICARD: So meditation.

00:00:08.150 --> 00:00:13.850
So first of all, meditation
is basically about silence.

00:00:13.850 --> 00:00:17.220
So I don't really need to come.

00:00:17.220 --> 00:00:20.010
And my dear mother
who's 92 said "silence

00:00:20.010 --> 00:00:24.370
is the language of the future."

00:00:24.370 --> 00:00:30.400
But since I came, I'll
just share a few words.

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:37.310
So I think in a way it's nice
in the kind of world we live,

00:00:37.310 --> 00:00:39.740
which is mostly a secular
world and although we

00:00:39.740 --> 00:00:43.480
have many other
options, meditation

00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:45.480
is a bit of a
culturally loaded word.

00:00:45.480 --> 00:00:50.930
We always think of something
exotic, not from here.

00:00:50.930 --> 00:00:53.750
And then also there are cliches
about meditation, like just

00:00:53.750 --> 00:00:56.310
empty your mind and relax.

00:00:56.310 --> 00:00:58.033
So relaxing, of
course we can do.

00:00:58.033 --> 00:00:58.824
Emptying your mind?

00:00:58.824 --> 00:01:02.180
I don't know how
long you can do that.

00:01:02.180 --> 00:01:06.070
But anyway, if you look
at the roots, in Sanskrit,

00:01:06.070 --> 00:01:09.150
bhavana means to cultivate.

00:01:09.150 --> 00:01:12.950
In Tibetan, [? gom ?] means to
become familiar with something.

00:01:12.950 --> 00:01:15.200
So obviously it's like training.

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:16.620
So what are you training?

00:01:16.620 --> 00:01:18.342
You play badminton or chess?

00:01:18.342 --> 00:01:21.550
They're not quite the same.

00:01:21.550 --> 00:01:25.710
So now familiarization can
also be cultivating a quality,

00:01:25.710 --> 00:01:30.930
like loving kindness,
mindfulness, open presence,

00:01:30.930 --> 00:01:35.510
pure awareness, loving
kindness, rejoicing,

00:01:35.510 --> 00:01:40.380
and so forth-- emotional
balance and all these things.

00:01:40.380 --> 00:01:42.904
And if you are going to teach
in schools or in enterprise,

00:01:42.904 --> 00:01:44.570
if you say we're going
to do medication,

00:01:44.570 --> 00:01:45.861
there might be some resistance.

00:01:45.861 --> 00:01:47.930
But if you say we
are going to help

00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:51.080
you to have better attention,
better emotionally balance,

00:01:51.080 --> 00:01:55.200
and better [? prosocial ?]
behavior, everybody goes wow.

00:01:55.200 --> 00:01:59.260
So familiarization
could be also not just

00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:00.970
captivating something
but becoming

00:02:00.970 --> 00:02:04.510
more familiar with the
nature of your mind.

00:02:04.510 --> 00:02:09.770
What is behind all of these
whirlpools of thoughts?

00:02:09.770 --> 00:02:13.670
Is there something
like a pure awareness

00:02:13.670 --> 00:02:18.390
that is free from mental
constructs, hope and fear, that

00:02:18.390 --> 00:02:22.490
is the most fundamental
aspect of mind from which

00:02:22.490 --> 00:02:29.830
all emotions, recollections,
reasoning, perceptions, inner

00:02:29.830 --> 00:02:32.200
and outer perceptions come.

00:02:32.200 --> 00:02:36.690
Without this luminous quality of
the mind, this basic cognitive

00:02:36.690 --> 00:02:38.780
faculty, none of it will happen.

00:02:38.780 --> 00:02:41.300
A glass doesn't think anything,
doesn't feel anything,

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:43.230
doesn't remember anything.

00:02:43.230 --> 00:02:47.440
It doesn't has this luminous
quality of cognition.

00:02:47.440 --> 00:02:52.570
So that basic nature that
we sometimes don't perceive

00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:56.060
because of so many
movements in the mind,

00:02:56.060 --> 00:02:58.220
we could also become
more familiar with that.

00:02:58.220 --> 00:03:01.610
And that's also one of
the aspects of meditation

00:03:01.610 --> 00:03:04.810
that doesn't necessarily need to
have an effortful cultivation.

00:03:04.810 --> 00:03:07.620
So all of those fall
within the scope

00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:09.480
of what we call meditation.

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:13.450
So as you see, it's a very
generic term, like training.

00:03:13.450 --> 00:03:18.840
So this is why the idea of
cultivating, familiarization--

00:03:18.840 --> 00:03:22.680
mind training tells more.

00:03:22.680 --> 00:03:26.020
So now again, what are
we going to train in?

00:03:26.020 --> 00:03:28.880
So mindfulness and
any other things

00:03:28.880 --> 00:03:32.840
related with presence, with
attention, is, of course,

00:03:32.840 --> 00:03:33.830
extremely useful.

00:03:33.830 --> 00:03:36.680
Because if your mind is
constantly distracted,

00:03:36.680 --> 00:03:39.780
you're going to
cultivate anything.

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:42.150
So that's why most
mediation begins

00:03:42.150 --> 00:03:46.770
with refining that tool of
mindfulness, and attention,

00:03:46.770 --> 00:03:49.590
and vigilance, and presence.

00:03:49.590 --> 00:03:52.460
And as you know,
since many of you

00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:55.637
are engaged both in
the well-being program,

00:03:55.637 --> 00:03:57.095
the search inside
yourself program,

00:03:57.095 --> 00:04:00.285
in this-- what do you call that?

00:04:00.285 --> 00:04:01.175
The G--

00:04:01.175 --> 00:04:02.070
AUDIENCE: G Pose.

00:04:02.070 --> 00:04:04.420
MATTHIEU RICARD: G Pose.

00:04:04.420 --> 00:04:06.500
In France, there's a
[? 3D ?] meditation

00:04:06.500 --> 00:04:08.090
that is sold on the internet.

00:04:08.090 --> 00:04:11.941
And you can get subscribed
for $30, $40, $50.

00:04:11.941 --> 00:04:14.440
And then depending on that, you
get more and more beautiful,

00:04:14.440 --> 00:04:17.550
young, and all kinds of things.

00:04:17.550 --> 00:04:18.470
I don't know.

00:04:18.470 --> 00:04:21.260
So I gather the G
Pose is not like that.

00:04:21.260 --> 00:04:25.400
So anyway to achieve
that as you do,

00:04:25.400 --> 00:04:30.942
a simple mind exercise to have a
clearer, more stable, more calm

00:04:30.942 --> 00:04:31.800
mind.

00:04:31.800 --> 00:04:35.390
And you do that often
with watching your breath.

00:04:35.390 --> 00:04:39.800
Why is this is a good
object of attention?

00:04:39.800 --> 00:04:42.530
Because you see, if you have
one of those red flashing lights

00:04:42.530 --> 00:04:45.650
as you find sometimes on the
highways, very aggressively

00:04:45.650 --> 00:04:48.430
flashing red lights, and it's
right in front of your eyes,

00:04:48.430 --> 00:04:51.650
and you say focus on that
and don't get distracted,

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:53.990
even if you're totally
distracted, you still see that.

00:04:53.990 --> 00:04:56.130
There's no way to escape.

00:04:56.130 --> 00:04:59.690
So there's no help to find
out whether you're distracted

00:04:59.690 --> 00:05:00.640
or not.

00:05:00.640 --> 00:05:03.320
But breath is
something invisible.

00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:05.940
You really have to pay attention
to be aware of the coming

00:05:05.940 --> 00:05:06.981
and going of your breath.

00:05:06.981 --> 00:05:09.670
If you are distracted,
it's gone because it

00:05:09.670 --> 00:05:13.260
doesn't impose itself to your
attention no matter what.

00:05:13.260 --> 00:05:16.180
So therefore it's a good
way to have something

00:05:16.180 --> 00:05:20.005
that is subtle enough that you
can realize that at some point

00:05:20.005 --> 00:05:22.130
that you have been distracted
because it's just not

00:05:22.130 --> 00:05:22.740
there anymore.

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:25.510
And you can bring
back your attention.

00:05:25.510 --> 00:05:28.010
So as you do often,
I'm share, for those

00:05:28.010 --> 00:05:30.600
who practice the
G Pose and Search

00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:34.950
Inside Yourself and well-being
program, so what do you do?

00:05:34.950 --> 00:05:36.114
Balance posture?

00:05:36.114 --> 00:05:37.530
You don't have to
torture yourself

00:05:37.530 --> 00:05:39.580
by trying to sit in
the full lotus posture

00:05:39.580 --> 00:05:41.780
unless it's natural to you.

00:05:41.780 --> 00:05:48.730
But the balance posture, not
to slack, or no self-induced

00:05:48.730 --> 00:05:50.980
torpor.

00:05:50.980 --> 00:05:53.290
Well, we call that in
the neuroscience lab

00:05:53.290 --> 00:06:00.230
the self-induced absorption
in cognitive opacity.

00:06:00.230 --> 00:06:02.290
Well, we don't want to do that.

00:06:02.290 --> 00:06:05.950
So a [? set ?] of clarity-- you
don't need to close your eyes.

00:06:05.950 --> 00:06:10.550
But you can just gaze
in a very panoramic way,

00:06:10.550 --> 00:06:13.350
not focusing on
anything and just simply

00:06:13.350 --> 00:06:16.420
be a aware of the coming
and going of the breath,

00:06:16.420 --> 00:06:21.670
a tickling, or warm, or cold
sensation, or the movement

00:06:21.670 --> 00:06:23.720
of your lungs or abdomen.

00:06:23.720 --> 00:06:27.420
And just keep on
that, very simply.

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:29.700
I've felt distracted, just
like the butterfly who

00:06:29.700 --> 00:06:32.890
goes out of the flower
and just come back.

00:06:32.890 --> 00:06:34.269
And don't make a fuss about it.

00:06:34.269 --> 00:06:35.310
Oh, I've been distracted.

00:06:35.310 --> 00:06:36.410
I'm no good.

00:06:36.410 --> 00:06:38.350
That's another kind
of distraction.

00:06:38.350 --> 00:06:41.274
If you are aware that you have
been distracted, that's it.

00:06:41.274 --> 00:06:42.190
You are mindful again.

00:06:42.190 --> 00:06:43.580
So that's.

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:47.560
Just resume your mindfulness.

00:06:47.560 --> 00:06:49.060
So let's do that
for a few moments

00:06:49.060 --> 00:06:52.740
and then see how we can
embed this caring dimension

00:06:52.740 --> 00:06:53.890
you into it after that.

00:07:46.060 --> 00:07:48.670
While you do that,
thoughts will come.

00:07:48.670 --> 00:07:50.460
Once they are there,
they are there.

00:07:50.460 --> 00:07:53.790
So there's no idea
of blocking them.

00:07:53.790 --> 00:07:56.810
But the problem is
not when they come.

00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:58.280
It's what you do after that.

00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:01.800
Do they proliferate or
do they just dissolve?

00:08:01.800 --> 00:08:03.510
That's the main thing.

00:08:03.510 --> 00:08:05.820
So imagine that a thought comes.

00:08:05.820 --> 00:08:07.170
Don't run after it.

00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:08.570
Don't try to block it.

00:08:08.570 --> 00:08:11.290
Let it pass like a bird
passing through the sky.

00:08:11.290 --> 00:08:13.385
If you do so, they
will not multiply.

00:08:35.200 --> 00:08:38.280
And if a bird passes
through the sky,

00:08:38.280 --> 00:08:42.690
you can still very well be
aware of the sky that has not

00:08:42.690 --> 00:08:44.910
changed behind the bird.

00:08:44.910 --> 00:08:47.895
So that's the pure
mindfulness or pure awareness.

00:09:33.780 --> 00:09:37.100
So imagine that you have
done that for 5, 10 minutes,

00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:40.900
whatever you can afford to do.

00:09:40.900 --> 00:09:45.820
Then you have a relatively more
clear, relatively more calm,

00:09:45.820 --> 00:09:47.840
relatively more
stable state of mind.

00:09:47.840 --> 00:09:50.460
That will come with practice.

00:09:50.460 --> 00:09:52.730
As you have seen with
the neuroscience data,

00:09:52.730 --> 00:09:57.130
anything you practice
will change what you are.

00:09:57.130 --> 00:10:00.940
So if you have done
that within a session,

00:10:00.940 --> 00:10:06.710
then you can use that calmer,
stable, more clear state

00:10:06.710 --> 00:10:09.910
to go to cultivate
something wholesome,

00:10:09.910 --> 00:10:13.610
like altruistic
love or compassion.

00:10:13.610 --> 00:10:17.050
So altruistic love, remember
that beautiful child

00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:21.860
we saw after the image of
saying man is a willful man?

00:10:21.860 --> 00:10:25.770
So when you see and think
of such a beautiful child,

00:10:25.770 --> 00:10:31.590
what do you wish except may
that child be safe, happy,

00:10:31.590 --> 00:10:35.710
may he or she flourish in life.

00:10:35.710 --> 00:10:38.260
May he spared
terrible suffering.

00:10:38.260 --> 00:10:39.890
May those who are
around him also

00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:41.830
enjoy a sense of flourishing.

00:10:41.830 --> 00:10:46.240
So just wishing
good to that person.

00:10:46.240 --> 00:10:48.450
So that's altruistic love.

00:10:48.450 --> 00:10:54.160
So let's start with something
easy, like this young child,

00:10:54.160 --> 00:10:57.730
and then we can extend it to
other people, like strangers.

00:10:57.730 --> 00:10:59.270
Why not?

00:10:59.270 --> 00:11:01.635
Why should the sun
not shine on everyone?

00:11:01.635 --> 00:11:03.370
It doesn't cost more.

00:11:03.370 --> 00:11:06.780
It's just a
qualitative experience,

00:11:06.780 --> 00:11:09.950
not like a keg that we
have limited resources of.

00:11:09.950 --> 00:11:13.730
Just extend that to all,
that same benevolence.

00:11:53.940 --> 00:11:56.780
Let this loving kindness
or this altruistic love

00:11:56.780 --> 00:12:01.260
completely fill your
mental landscape.

00:12:01.260 --> 00:12:03.350
If you are distracted,
come back to it.

00:12:03.350 --> 00:12:06.390
If it sort of becomes
dim, revive it.

00:12:06.390 --> 00:12:08.070
So nourish it.

00:12:08.070 --> 00:12:16.160
Keep its quality
vivid, intense, clear.

00:12:33.930 --> 00:12:36.730
And then if you
think how could I

00:12:36.730 --> 00:12:39.870
do that with bloody dictators?

00:12:39.870 --> 00:12:44.160
So in that case, it's
not wishing success

00:12:44.160 --> 00:12:50.280
to that person's
terrible projects.

00:12:50.280 --> 00:12:53.410
It's not liking that person.

00:12:53.410 --> 00:12:57.120
You can have total disgust
for the person's action,

00:12:57.120 --> 00:13:01.515
but still what shape
would altruistic love

00:13:01.515 --> 00:13:04.590
take in front of this dictator?

00:13:04.590 --> 00:13:08.050
It becomes a wish of compassion.

00:13:08.050 --> 00:13:12.950
May the suffering and the causes
of suffering be dispelled.

00:13:12.950 --> 00:13:16.510
And of course, a dictator is
a cause of immense suffering.

00:13:16.510 --> 00:13:20.290
So you might wish may his
action be counteracted.

00:13:20.290 --> 00:13:23.700
May the cruelty, the
difference indifference,

00:13:23.700 --> 00:13:28.570
the greed that motivates such
a destructive state of mind

00:13:28.570 --> 00:13:29.480
be dispelled.

00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:30.990
That, you can wish, of course.

00:13:39.030 --> 00:13:41.690
So that's how we can
shift to compassion.

00:13:41.690 --> 00:13:47.190
Compassion is not fundamentally
different from altruistic love.

00:13:47.190 --> 00:13:49.470
Altruistic love was
wishing everyone happiness

00:13:49.470 --> 00:13:51.710
and the cause of happiness.

00:13:51.710 --> 00:13:55.230
When it meets suffering,
it becomes compassion,

00:13:55.230 --> 00:13:59.220
which is the shape that
altruistic love takes

00:13:59.220 --> 00:14:01.200
when it encounters suffering.

00:14:01.200 --> 00:14:05.070
It is the wish may the beings
suffering and the cause

00:14:05.070 --> 00:14:06.670
suffering be dispelled.

00:14:06.670 --> 00:14:10.210
So for that, we may
visualize intense suffering--

00:14:10.210 --> 00:14:12.440
and there's so many
in this world--

00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:17.170
and wish those beings be
spared that suffering,

00:14:17.170 --> 00:14:20.110
the causes of
suffering be remedied--

00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:21.915
a sort of intense compassion.

00:15:18.760 --> 00:15:22.440
And if you feel somehow
overwhelmed by the magnitude

00:15:22.440 --> 00:15:26.400
of suffering, you
should think that this

00:15:26.400 --> 00:15:30.310
needs to be met not with some
kind of empathic distress

00:15:30.310 --> 00:15:32.700
but with a magnitude of
compassionate courage.

00:15:53.860 --> 00:15:55.980
Then sometimes,
we must still feel

00:15:55.980 --> 00:15:58.400
overwhelmed by so
much suffering.

00:15:58.400 --> 00:16:03.180
Though then we can also
think of wonderful people who

00:16:03.180 --> 00:16:06.470
are imbued with such
great quantities

00:16:06.470 --> 00:16:10.690
of compassion, of
knowledge, of wisdom,

00:16:10.690 --> 00:16:15.650
of dedication to
others-- social workers,

00:16:15.650 --> 00:16:18.300
spiritual teachers,
great luminaries,

00:16:18.300 --> 00:16:22.730
those who bring new ideas
into this world and rejoice.

00:16:22.730 --> 00:16:26.430
Without any other thoughts,
just fully appreciate them.

00:16:26.430 --> 00:16:28.800
It's a very altruistic
thing to rejoice.

00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:30.550
Because there's nothing
to gain from that.

00:16:30.550 --> 00:16:35.290
Nobody's going to praise you if
you rejoice in Gandhi's life.

00:16:35.290 --> 00:16:36.810
Nobody's going to
blame you if you

00:16:36.810 --> 00:16:39.820
don't have this state of mind.

00:16:39.820 --> 00:16:41.050
They won't know.

00:16:41.050 --> 00:16:45.830
So it's really part
of altruism to rejoice

00:16:45.830 --> 00:16:47.828
in the goodness of others,
and their qualities,

00:16:47.828 --> 00:16:48.536
and achievements.

00:17:11.220 --> 00:17:13.069
And rejoicing is
also the antidote

00:17:13.069 --> 00:17:16.410
to envy, jealousy, feeling
miserable because others have

00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:19.339
quality, which is pretty silly.

00:17:41.065 --> 00:17:44.770
And besides altruistic
love, compassion,

00:17:44.770 --> 00:17:47.480
rejoicing and
celebrating, there's

00:17:47.480 --> 00:17:49.060
a fourth thing that we need.

00:17:49.060 --> 00:17:51.890
That's impartiality.

00:17:51.890 --> 00:17:56.800
We cannot know compassion--
and altruism is not a reward

00:17:56.800 --> 00:18:01.100
for good behavior or for
the way people treat you.

00:18:01.100 --> 00:18:06.210
Compassion aims at removing
any suffering wherever

00:18:06.210 --> 00:18:10.020
it is, however it manifests.

00:18:10.020 --> 00:18:11.310
So it's not a moral judgement.

00:18:11.310 --> 00:18:13.380
Moral judgement
exists, but it's not

00:18:13.380 --> 00:18:14.810
about the way people behave.

00:18:14.810 --> 00:18:18.160
It's about remedying
the causes of suffering.

00:18:18.160 --> 00:18:24.160
Therefore, that we wish to
dispel the causes of suffering

00:18:24.160 --> 00:18:29.400
can apply to all-- close
persons, strangers, even

00:18:29.400 --> 00:18:31.070
obnoxious people.

00:18:31.070 --> 00:18:33.720
So we need that powerful
wish, like the sun,

00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:35.450
which shines on everything.

00:18:35.450 --> 00:18:36.950
And when some
people tell you how

00:18:36.950 --> 00:18:39.380
can I not love more my
children, and my dear

00:18:39.380 --> 00:18:41.470
ones, and my companions,
and so forth?

00:18:41.470 --> 00:18:43.020
Yes, of course.

00:18:43.020 --> 00:18:45.770
No, if the sun shines, if
life circumstances bring

00:18:45.770 --> 00:18:48.110
them very close to you, they
get naturally more light

00:18:48.110 --> 00:18:48.750
and more warm.

00:18:48.750 --> 00:18:50.840
But it's not at the
cost of discriminating.

00:18:50.840 --> 00:18:53.210
Just they happen to be there.

00:18:53.210 --> 00:18:55.580
But the sun still
shines on everyone.

00:18:55.580 --> 00:18:58.680
If you are to concentrate
your reserves on those people,

00:18:58.680 --> 00:19:02.420
actually, you will shine
less well, less intensely,

00:19:02.420 --> 00:19:03.510
with less light on those.

00:19:03.510 --> 00:19:06.640
So everyone is losing.

00:19:06.640 --> 00:19:08.390
By having this attitude
to all, you also

00:19:08.390 --> 00:19:10.780
love better your loved ones.

00:19:10.780 --> 00:19:14.130
So this is a much
better situation.

00:19:14.130 --> 00:19:17.750
Just extend your altruistic
love, your compassion to all.

00:19:17.750 --> 00:19:18.875
That's called impartiality.

00:19:43.880 --> 00:19:45.880
So of course, we did that
for a very short time.

00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:48.970
But you can see you could
expend those periods of silence,

00:19:48.970 --> 00:19:50.920
which are the real thing.

00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:53.330
And then also you can
switch between those.

00:19:53.330 --> 00:19:55.890
For instance, if altruistic
love turns a little bit

00:19:55.890 --> 00:19:59.330
into attachment, then
go to impartiality.

00:19:59.330 --> 00:20:02.500
If impartiality becomes
a bit of indifference--

00:20:02.500 --> 00:20:06.080
you're impartial, but
you're not caring very much,

00:20:06.080 --> 00:20:07.120
then move to compassion.

00:20:07.120 --> 00:20:09.160
Think of the
suffering of beings.

00:20:09.160 --> 00:20:11.400
And if you're overwhelmed
at some point,

00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:13.560
then move again to rejoicing.

00:20:13.560 --> 00:20:16.910
So likewise, skillfully,
by combining those four,

00:20:16.910 --> 00:20:19.330
then the four of
them go together.

00:20:19.330 --> 00:20:24.566
And then you get this profound,
you could say, good heart

00:20:24.566 --> 00:20:27.320
or good-heartedness, this
is fundamental quality

00:20:27.320 --> 00:20:28.830
of goodness.

00:20:28.830 --> 00:20:31.580
So that's what
meditation is about.

00:20:31.580 --> 00:20:35.360
So you see, of course,
mindfulness is a precious tool,

00:20:35.360 --> 00:20:37.870
and it does extreme
good in the world,

00:20:37.870 --> 00:20:41.360
in the clinical world, in the
world of the working place,

00:20:41.360 --> 00:20:43.320
and many other areas.

00:20:43.320 --> 00:20:48.460
But I think if we never lose
sight that mindfulness should

00:20:48.460 --> 00:20:55.430
go always and unambiguously
with a caring quality,

00:20:55.430 --> 00:21:00.190
then it will have its full
potential to help you, I think,

00:21:00.190 --> 00:21:01.380
even more.

00:21:01.380 --> 00:21:04.120
So thank you.

00:21:04.120 --> 00:21:08.255
And at the end of any
practice, in the same way

00:21:08.255 --> 00:21:10.320
at the beginning, which
is why I'm doing that,

00:21:10.320 --> 00:21:12.930
not just for me, for all
sentient beings, at the end,

00:21:12.930 --> 00:21:15.930
at the conclusion,
dedicate whatever good we

00:21:15.930 --> 00:21:18.680
did this morning, may
that benefit everyone.

00:21:18.680 --> 00:21:19.180
Why not?

00:21:19.180 --> 00:21:22.130
And it's not like a piece of
cake that you put in pieces.

00:21:22.130 --> 00:21:23.910
Everyone gets everything.

00:21:23.910 --> 00:21:25.570
That's a good deal.

00:21:25.570 --> 00:21:26.170
So thank you.

00:21:26.170 --> 00:21:29.560
So if you have any
questions, welcome.

00:21:33.862 --> 00:21:35.300
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

